Stockwell v. Boyce. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. May 24, 1889.) Appeal from judgmetit on report of referee.

Argued before Van Brunt, P. J., and Bartlett and Macomber, JJ.

Billings <& Cardozo, (Michael H. Cardozo, of counsel,) for appellant. Marsh, Wilson & Wallis, ( William G. Wilson, of counsel,) for respondent. Van Brunt, P. J.

We are of the opinion that the judgment'in this case should be affirmed, for the reasons stated in the decision in the case of Masterton v. Boyce, 6 N. Y. Supp. 65, handed down herewith. All concur.
